DESCRIPTION:Little Swimmers is a darkly funny hybrid of theatre\, stand-up\
 , and storytelling about one man’s hilariously messy quest to become a fa
 ther. Battling his own body\, a bewildered urologist\, and an embarrassing 
 admiration for Tom Cruise\, he spirals through fertility clinics\, panic\, 
 and moments of unnecessary humiliation. What starts as a simple plan to hav
 e a baby quickly turns into a chaotic obsession involving babies\, spiralli
 ng self-doubt\, and a growing suspicion that everyone around him became an 
 adult years ago. As the pressure builds\, so does his desperation to hold o
 nto control\, dignity\, and the last scraps of his shrinking masculinity. A
 bsurd\, personal\, and painfully honest\, Little Swimmers is a show about f
 ailing bodies\, fragile egos\, and the strange stories we tell ourselves wh
 en life doesn’t go to plan. A funny\, raw\, and slightly unhinged look at
  modern manhood\, growing up\, and what happens when your swimmers refuse t
 o cooperate. Laugh. Wince. Squirm.\nMore info: https://comedyatlas.app/come
 dy-atlas/event/little-swimmers/
